# Architecture

This variant uses a lightweight hexagonal layout.

## Structure

- `src/{{ project_module }}/main.py`
  Thin process entrypoint.

- `src/{{ project_module }}/app.py`
  Application composition root.

- `src/{{ project_module }}/cli/commands.py`
  CLI layer and command definitions.

- `src/{{ project_module }}/application/use_cases/`
  Use cases and system operation orchestration.

- `src/{{ project_module }}/application/dto/`
  Input and output objects for use cases.

- `src/{{ project_module }}/application/ports/`
  Contracts required by the application layer.

- `src/{{ project_module }}/domain/`
  Domain model: entities and value objects.

- `src/{{ project_module }}/adapters/repositories/`
  Repository and storage port implementations.

- `src/{{ project_module }}/adapters/clients/`
  HTTP integrations, external API clients, and other technical integrations.

## Boundaries

- `main.py` starts the application
- `app.py` wires dependencies
- `cli/` contains the input layer
- `application/` contains use cases, DTOs, and ports
- `domain/` contains the domain model
- `adapters/` contains technical implementations
